{
  "texts": [
    "in vivo properties comparable to those of immune-system-derived antibodies.",
    "AbNatiV consists of a vector-quantized variational auto-encoder (VQ-VAE) designed to process aligned Fv sequences and trained with masked unsupervised learning on sequences from curated native immune repertoires.",
    "Four different models are trained on the Fv sequences of human heavy chains (VH), kappa light chains (Vκ), lambda light chains (Vλ) and camelid heavy-chain single-domains (VHH).",
    "AbNatiV can assess separately the degree of humanness and of VHH nativeness of a given Fv sequence.",
    "It provides both an interpretable overall nativeness score and a residue-level nativeness profile of the Fv sequence, which can guide engineering by highlighting sequence regions harbouring liabilities."
  ]
}